        <p>The skilled employee category suits professionals meeting the income threshold (currently AED 30,000 monthly) with a bachelor's degree or equivalent. This is the most common Golden Visa category for <a href="/locations/dubai/">Dubai</a> residents working in finance, technology, healthcare, and other professional sectors.</p>
        
        <p>Your document package will typically include: degree certificate with MOHESR equivalency, salary certificate, employment contract, and passport copies. If sponsoring family members, add marriage certificates, children's birth certificates, and potentially previous marriage documentation if applicable.</p>
        
        <p>The timeline from document preparation to visa issuance varies. Translation itself takes 2-3 days for a complete package. MOHESR equivalency adds 5-15 working days depending on the institution. ICP processing then takes its own course. We help you plan realistically based on current processing times.</p>
        
        <h3>Investor Golden Visa</h3>
        <p>Property investors with holdings worth AED 2 million or more can apply for the investor Golden Visa. The key documents here are property-related: title deeds, valuation certificates (if required), and proof of ownership.</p>
        
        <p>Many <a href="/locations/dubai/palm-jumeirah/">Palm Jumeirah</a> property owners pursue this category. We already handle their property documentation—title deeds, SPAs, and POAs—so adding Golden Visa translation is a natural extension of existing relationships.</p>
        
        <p>Business investors have different requirements including company documents, financial statements, and evidence of investment value. For those with substantial corporate holdings, we coordinate with <a href="/services/corporate-translation/">corporate translation services</a> to prepare comprehensive packages.</p>
        
        <h3>Specialized Talent Categories</h3>
        <p>Doctors, scientists, researchers, artists, and athletes may qualify under specialized talent categories. Each has its own criteria and documentation requirements.</p>
        
        <p>Medical professionals need translated medical licenses, specialty certificates, and evidence of practice. The Dubai Health Authority licensing process has its own translation requirements which we also support.</p>
        
        <p>Researchers and scientists may need to evidence publications, patents, or institutional affiliations. Artists require proof of recognition in their field. We advise on what documentation is typically required for each specialty.</p>
        
        <h3>Family Member Sponsorship</h3>
        <p>Golden Visa holders can sponsor immediate family members, creating a path to long-term UAE residency for the whole family. Spouses require <a href="/personal/vital-records/marriage/">marriage certificate translation</a>; children require <a href="/personal/vital-records/birth/">birth certificate translation</a>.</p>
        
        <p>For complex family situations—previous marriages, adopted children, or adult dependents—additional documentation may be required. We can advise on the typical requirements based on your specific circumstances.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
