      <h2>Working With Us</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <h3>Document Review Process</h3>
        <p>Before we begin translation, we review your documents to ensure they contain what ICP requires. This avoids situations where you receive a perfect translation of an incomplete document. If your salary certificate lacks the permanent employment statement, we will tell you before we translate it—not after.</p>
        
        <p>We also check for attestation requirements. Documents from certain countries need attestation before they can be used in the UAE. We can advise whether your documents need this step and coordinate the process if so.</p>
        
        <h3>Coordination and Communication</h3>
        <p>Golden Visa applications involve multiple documents, often arriving at different times. A salary certificate might be issued today; a degree is already in hand; birth certificates for children are being requested from another country. We track all components and keep you informed of what is ready and what is still needed.</p>
        
        <p>Our WhatsApp coordination means you can check status, submit additional documents, or ask questions at any time. We understand that Golden Visa applications are time-sensitive, often tied to visa renewals or employment changes.</p>
        
        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <p>The best starting point is to send us what you have. Even if your document package is incomplete, we can review what exists, advise on what else is needed, and begin translation on the documents that are ready.</p>
        
        <p>Many clients are uncertain about their eligibility or requirements. A brief WhatsApp conversation usually clarifies which category applies to you and what documents you will need. We can then provide an accurate quote for the complete package.</p>
      </div>
